                    <ab>(C) <persName key="#Popes" ref="#people/70">Sergius</persName>
                        <rs key="#Popes">episcopus, servus servorum Dei</rs>, dilecto <persName
                            key="#Abbots">
                            <rs key="#Abbots">. . . monachum adque abbatem</rs>
                        </persName>
                        <orgName key="#Monasteries">
                            <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterii</rs> sanctorum Christi martirum
                            Stephani et Silvestri adque Dionisii</orgName> et per te in eodem
                        venerabili monasterio . . . . [Petentium desideriis ita nos convenit]
                        impertire assensum at tamen nul . . . . . . tti dispendiis ea que pro
                        restauratione predicti monasterii <geogName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Allocation_to_churches #Rent_in_money #Clusae/gates"
                            >concedimus perpetuo <rs key="#Clusae/gates">porta</rs> que vocatur
                                <placeName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Rent_in_money #Clusae/gates"
                                ref="#places/305">Sancti Valentini</placeName>,</geogName> fundatas
                        et coniunctas dum claudendum aperiendum vestri custodes phu . . . . . . .
                        ingrediendi et egrediendi quicquid exigitur et fuerit ph . . . cum terra
                        intus et phoris ad eius porte, nostre pertinen . . . concedimus vobis <rs
                            key="#Monasteries">monasterium</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Monasteries">Sancti Valentini</orgName> phoris eadem porta .
                        . . . sive et <geogName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Rent_in_money #Bridges/pontoons #Tolls"
                                ><rs key="#Bridges/pontoons">ponte lapideo</rs> qui appellatur
                                <placeName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Rent_in_money #Bridges/pontoons #Tolls"
                                ref="#places/304">Molvium</placeName></geogName>
                        <rs key="#Tolls">cum omni datione</rs> . . . . <rs key="#Rivers">fluvium
                            Tyberis</rs>. Hec omnia, ut dictum est, a presenti prima indictione ita
                        sane ut vobis singulis quibus rationibus ecclesiasticis <rs
                            key="#Rent_in_money">auri solidis (C) TRES (C)</rs> difficultate . . .
                        statuentes apostolica censura sub divini iudicii, obtestatione anathematis
                        interdictum ut nulli umquam successorum nostrorum pontificum hec . . .
                        monasterio molestari vel alienare, set qui hoc presumpserit persona qui eas
                        contendit adversus vestro monasterio, sit a regno Dei alienus et vinculo sit
                        innodatus in infernus, et cum Diabulo adque cum Iuda traditore domini nostri
                        Ihesu Christi, aeterni incendii deputatus . . . intuito observatores in
                        omnibus et iam dicto vestro monasterio defensores . . . a misericordiissimo
                        domino Deo nostro consequar, et vitae eternae . . . amen. Scriptum per manus
                            <persName key="#Papal_court_officer #Scriniarius #Judge"
                            >Gaudiosus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Papal_court_officer #Scriniarius #Judge">protoscrinius</rs> sancte
                        Romane ecclesie indictione suprascripta prima. â€  Bene valete. [Datum] . . .
                        regionarii et bliviothecarium sancte Romane Ecclesie, <date>anno Deo
                            propitio, pontificatus domini <persName key="#Popes" ref="#people/70"
                                >Sergii secundi</persName>
                            <rs key="#Popes">pape</rs>, anno primo, regnante <persName
                                key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/9">Lothario</persName>
                            <rs key="#Emperor/king">a Deo coronato imperatore</rs> indictione
                            suprascripta prima</date>.</ab>
